# Metadata EUI polish

When editing governed renderers, surface builders, or Pattern B/C pages under the globs above, **apply `.agents/skills/metadata-eui-polish/SKILL.md` automatically**.

Do not invoke `shadcn-metadata`, `web-design-guidelines`, or `vercel-composition-patterns` as separate workflows for the same task — the metadata EUI skill composes them.

Hard contracts (always enforce):

- `.cursor/rules/governed-renderer-contract.mdc` — `@container`, `dataNature`, no raw leaf `<div>`
- `.cursor/rules/governed-surface-schema-contract.mdc` — Zod configuration schemas
- `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` — semantic tokens only

Post-task: targeted ESLint on touched renderer paths + `pnpm typecheck`. Renderer changes also run `pnpm lint:renderer-skeleton-parity` when skeleton geometry changes.
